535
00:40:17,123 --> 00:40:18,624
But it's still expensive.

536
00:40:18,707 --> 00:40:20,126
Gosh.

537
00:40:21,252 --> 00:40:22,878
Are you Mr. Oh Han-gyeol?

538
00:40:23,295 --> 00:40:24,296
Yes.

539
00:40:26,382 --> 00:40:27,383
What's this?

540
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:29,927
Excuse me. What's this?

541
00:40:31,387 --> 00:40:32,388
Excuse...

542
00:40:38,644 --> 00:40:39,687
What is it?

543
00:40:54,577 --> 00:40:56,912
Oh, my. What's this?

544
00:40:59,248 --> 00:41:01,584
Mr. Oh, I'm over here.

545
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:03,961
-Come in.
-Okay.

546
00:41:08,883 --> 00:41:10,342
-Have a seat.
-Okay.

547
00:41:13,387 --> 00:41:16,932
Ms. Park, you caught me off guard.

548
00:41:17,349 --> 00:41:18,976
Do you see me sweating here?

549
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:21,812
This...

550
00:41:22,521 --> 00:41:25,024
never happened.

551
00:41:27,318 --> 00:41:30,571
Mr. Oh, I really don't understand you.

552
00:41:31,655 --> 00:41:34,950
Are you really that innocent
or are you just pretending to be?

553
00:41:35,034 --> 00:41:37,328
No. I'm not innocent.

554
00:41:37,411 --> 00:41:38,537
But...

555
00:41:39,622 --> 00:41:42,833
this is not about me
being innocent or not.

556
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:47,046
You're not helping Hwi-yeong at all
by doing this.

557
00:41:47,338 --> 00:41:49,173
Hwi-yeong is already doing great.

558
00:41:49,256 --> 00:41:52,384
Couldn't you just trust him and wait...

559
00:41:52,468 --> 00:41:53,469
Mr. Oh.

560
00:41:55,012 --> 00:41:57,097
Why do you have to make
such a big deal out of it?

561
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:58,974
I really don't understand.

562
00:41:59,058 --> 00:42:01,435
Why can't you just smooth things over?

563
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:10,611
Did you do this to Mr. Kim,
the previous homeroom teacher too?

564
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:12,780
Did you do this then too?

565
00:42:14,907 --> 00:42:15,824
Ma'am.

566
00:42:16,742 --> 00:42:20,162
If you did, I think this is
a very serious situation.

567
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:21,288
So?

568
00:42:21,413 --> 00:42:24,375
Did you keep calling Mr. Kim

569
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:25,793
to find out about this?

570
00:42:25,876 --> 00:42:27,711
What were you trying to dig up?

571
00:42:27,962 --> 00:42:31,131
Is that what Mr. Kim said?

572
00:42:33,509 --> 00:42:36,428
Mr. Oh. I have just one favor
to ask of you.

573
00:42:36,595 --> 00:42:40,808
At least until Hwi-yeong gets into
Seoul National University, can't you...

574
00:42:42,518 --> 00:42:44,436
Can't you please just stay quiet?

575
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:47,898
Your ridiculous sense of justice

576
00:42:47,982 --> 00:42:52,194
may destroy my Hwi-yeong's future.
I don't even want to imagine that.

577
00:42:52,528 --> 00:42:55,030
Please, I'm begging you.

578
00:42:55,281 --> 00:42:58,701
Mr. Oh? You understand
what I'm getting at, right?

579
00:43:00,828 --> 00:43:03,289
I feel like crap.

580
00:43:08,127 --> 00:43:10,504
What does she take me for?

581
00:43:17,219 --> 00:43:19,096
Please take my order.

582
00:43:23,642 --> 00:43:25,519
This world stinks.

583
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:29,523
How could I fail again?

584
00:43:49,001 --> 00:43:50,377
See? It's not bad, right?

585
00:43:51,045 --> 00:43:52,755
It's a little less lonely

586
00:43:53,005 --> 00:43:55,049
-when we drink together.
-Yes.

587
00:43:55,132 --> 00:43:58,385
That's right. You got that right.

588
00:43:59,345 --> 00:44:03,057
My mom always told me she wanted me...

589
00:44:03,682 --> 00:44:06,769
to always be an upright...

590
00:44:08,228 --> 00:44:10,481
An upright person.

591
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:13,942
That's what my mom always wanted me to be.

592
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:17,321
Mom...

593
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:22,534
My mom is working hard
and suffering in the countryside.

594
00:44:23,952 --> 00:44:26,955
I'm sorry, Mom. I failed again.

595
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:28,832
Darn it.

596
00:44:34,296 --> 00:44:37,132
Why are you crying?

597
00:44:38,967 --> 00:44:40,511
You're making me cry.

598
00:44:40,678 --> 00:44:41,929
Don't cry.

599
00:44:45,224 --> 00:44:46,850
I'm terrible.

600
00:44:47,184 --> 00:44:50,396
-No, I'm worse.
-No.

601
00:44:51,814 --> 00:44:54,233
I'm so terrible, Mom...

602
00:44:59,154 --> 00:45:01,240
-Mr. Oh, are you okay?
-Yes, I'm fine.

603
00:45:01,323 --> 00:45:03,200
I called a cab. Wait a minute.

604
00:45:03,283 --> 00:45:05,994
-I... I'll take you home.
-No.

605
00:45:06,078 --> 00:45:08,038
-Wait a minute, okay?
-Okay.

606
00:45:08,247 --> 00:45:09,498
What's taking him so long?

607
00:45:12,793 --> 00:45:15,379
There he is. Mr. Oh, your cab's here.

608
00:45:15,879 --> 00:45:17,172
-Let's go.
-Okay.

609
00:45:17,256 --> 00:45:18,841
I'll take you home.

610
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:20,801
-Here. Are you okay?
-Yes.

611
00:45:20,884 --> 00:45:22,594
I'm totally fine.

612
00:45:22,678 --> 00:45:24,221
-No, no.
-I am...

613
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:28,934
-I'm sorry. Are you okay?
-I'm okay.

614
00:45:29,476 --> 00:45:31,186
I'm okay. Go first.

615
00:45:31,270 --> 00:45:33,230
-Get in.
-Okay.

616
00:45:35,357 --> 00:45:36,567
Where do you live again?

617
00:45:36,650 --> 00:45:39,278
Deullae Apartments on Cheonbongsan Road.

618
00:45:39,361 --> 00:45:40,779
Deullae Apartments, please.

619
00:45:40,863 --> 00:45:42,948
Take him home safely. Bye.

620
00:45:45,075 --> 00:45:46,452
Bye.

621
00:45:48,996 --> 00:45:50,038
Song-hui.

622
00:45:51,331 --> 00:45:52,958
It's so annoying.

623
00:45:54,501 --> 00:45:55,961
Why am I mad?

624
00:45:56,170 --> 00:45:58,505
It's not like I didn't know.

625
00:45:59,465 --> 00:46:01,049
He isn't worth getting mad about.

626
00:46:01,925 --> 00:46:03,051
Mom.

627
00:46:03,844 --> 00:46:05,262
You should've taken a day off.

628
00:46:05,345 --> 00:46:07,431
How did you drive with your arm like that?

629
00:46:07,514 --> 00:46:10,142
I hired someone to drive me around

630
00:46:10,350 --> 00:46:12,060
and help with housework.

631
00:46:14,062 --> 00:46:16,356
-What?
-That's good.

632
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,111
Hold on.

633
00:46:22,821 --> 00:46:24,448
What are you doing? I'm not a kid.

634
00:46:25,365 --> 00:46:28,327
What? Things like this
become fond memories.

635
00:46:29,953 --> 00:46:33,999
There's a kid in my class
who draws these things well.

636
00:46:34,541 --> 00:46:35,918
They should go to art school.

637
00:46:39,254 --> 00:46:40,464
Is something bothering you?

638
00:46:42,591 --> 00:46:43,592
No.

639
00:46:45,719 --> 00:46:47,596
-Mom.
-Yes?

640
00:46:48,096 --> 00:46:50,182
Was Dad your first love?

641
00:46:51,225 --> 00:46:53,477
That's right. I was 18.

642
00:46:56,355 --> 00:47:00,192
I guess first loves end easily
and become meaningless.

643
00:47:01,443 --> 00:47:02,819
Listen to this kid.

644
00:47:02,903 --> 00:47:06,281
Why is it meaningless? First love is huge.

645
00:47:07,115 --> 00:47:10,160
It feels like
you're walking down the street,

646
00:47:10,244 --> 00:47:14,248
and someone's suddenly throwing
a bucket of water at you.

647
00:47:15,374 --> 00:47:17,668
It's like having some emotion

648
00:47:17,751 --> 00:47:20,629
pounce on you.
That's what your first love is.

649
00:47:22,005 --> 00:47:24,675
It makes you forget who you used to be

650
00:47:24,758 --> 00:47:26,843
before the water was thrown at you.

651
00:47:27,094 --> 00:47:31,223
Hey. That kid in your class who was
forced to transfer... The cute kid.

652
00:47:31,306 --> 00:47:33,976
Is he still in your group
for the performance assessment?

653
00:47:35,644 --> 00:47:38,313
No, it's over now.

654
00:47:38,981 --> 00:47:39,982
Okay.

655
00:47:41,316 --> 00:47:42,568
That's good.

656
00:47:50,993 --> 00:47:52,077
What is that?

657
00:47:53,036 --> 00:47:54,079
Peas.

658
00:47:54,663 --> 00:47:58,333
Because you're not the same person
you used to be anymore.

659
00:47:58,500 --> 00:48:00,711
The person you used to be
before you met your first love.

660
00:48:03,505 --> 00:48:05,299
I wish I could go back to those times.

661
00:48:07,175 --> 00:48:09,386
We met when we were too immature,

662
00:48:09,469 --> 00:48:12,055
so we ended up breaking up,

663
00:48:12,431 --> 00:48:13,849
but I have no regrets.

664
00:48:14,391 --> 00:48:16,268
That's just how it is.

665
00:48:19,605 --> 00:48:21,481
What am I saying in front of my child?

666
00:48:23,108 --> 00:48:24,109
All done.

667
00:48:24,276 --> 00:48:26,278
Wash up and go to bed.

668
00:48:26,862 --> 00:48:28,905
We finished so quickly.

669
00:48:33,243 --> 00:48:35,245
Come to think of it,
I can't remember either.

670
00:48:35,746 --> 00:48:37,539
The person I used to be
before I met Soo-bin.

671
00:48:39,708 --> 00:48:42,002
Excuse me! You in the checkered shirt...

672
00:48:42,461 --> 00:48:43,754
Are you all right?

673
00:48:49,968 --> 00:48:53,096
From that moment on, I stopped
being the person I used to be.

674
00:48:57,142 --> 00:48:58,769
Okay. Gosh.

675
00:49:00,020 --> 00:49:01,313
Did I gain weight?

676
00:49:01,605 --> 00:49:03,106
I feel sick.

677
00:49:06,401 --> 00:49:07,778
You're so handsome.

678
00:49:08,403 --> 00:49:10,656
Hold on. Where's my bag?

679
00:49:10,739 --> 00:49:13,241
My bag...

680
00:49:15,452 --> 00:49:16,662
My bag...

681
00:49:27,756 --> 00:49:30,550
I'd like to drive you,
but I feel bad asking the driver.

682
00:49:30,926 --> 00:49:32,761
It's okay. I like this better.

683
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:36,014
Are you saying you didn't like
having me drive you?

684
00:49:36,098 --> 00:49:38,392
Come on. That's not what I meant.

685
00:49:39,226 --> 00:49:40,310
Bye.

686
00:49:40,769 --> 00:49:42,187
-Have a nice day.
-Thanks.

687
00:49:43,021 --> 00:49:44,272
That's so funny.

688
00:49:48,235 --> 00:49:49,444
Study hard.

689
00:49:49,695 --> 00:49:51,071
Get your head on straight.

690
00:50:00,414 --> 00:50:01,581
Hello.

691
00:50:01,665 --> 00:50:03,125
Were you hiding there?

692
00:50:04,126 --> 00:50:06,420
Yes, I felt a bit... You know.

693
00:50:07,129 --> 00:50:09,131
I brought some young radish kimchi.

694
00:50:09,214 --> 00:50:11,883
We should put it in the kimchi fridge
before we go.

695
00:50:11,967 --> 00:50:13,176
The kimchi fridge?

696
00:50:14,469 --> 00:50:15,554
You didn't have to.

697
00:50:42,164 --> 00:50:43,498
You guys are still...

698
00:50:46,293 --> 00:50:47,753
Math is next, right?

699
00:50:50,964 --> 00:50:52,507
They still are.

700
00:50:58,513 --> 00:51:01,016
-What's this?
-What?

701
00:51:02,601 --> 00:51:03,769
What's wrong with this?

702
00:51:03,977 --> 00:51:04,978
My gosh.

703
00:51:05,479 --> 00:51:06,688
Who did this?

704
00:51:08,774 --> 00:51:10,358
What is this? A wire?

705
00:51:10,442 --> 00:51:11,777
Don't. You'll hurt your hand.

706
00:51:13,403 --> 00:51:14,613
What is this?

707
00:51:23,038 --> 00:51:25,415
Oh, no. Oh, boy.

708
00:51:28,168 --> 00:51:29,628
-What are you doing?
-What?

709
00:51:30,295 --> 00:51:31,254
What are you doing?

710
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:32,839
Oh, sorry.

711
00:51:32,923 --> 00:51:34,049
I slipped.

712
00:51:35,592 --> 00:51:36,802
You hid my math book,

713
00:51:36,885 --> 00:51:38,261
wrapped that wire around my bag,

714
00:51:38,345 --> 00:51:40,555
and put that ladybug
in my tray too, didn't you?

715
00:51:40,639 --> 00:51:41,556
Me?

716
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:43,308
No, I didn't.

717
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:44,810
Is it because of Ro-mi?

718
00:51:45,268 --> 00:51:46,311
No.

719
00:51:46,770 --> 00:51:49,439
Hey. You should try harder
to make Ro-mi like you then.

720
00:51:49,523 --> 00:51:50,816
Instead of taking it out on me.

721
00:51:50,899 --> 00:51:51,858
How?

722
00:51:51,942 --> 00:51:54,820
All she does is stare at you
all the time. What should I do?

723
00:51:57,948 --> 00:52:00,242
Jun-u, you're really...

724
00:52:01,701 --> 00:52:03,245
You should leave! Just transfer!

725
00:52:03,328 --> 00:52:05,956
Go to another school! Get lost!

726
00:52:07,541 --> 00:52:09,876
Are you laughing? Is that funny, you punk?

727
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:11,419
-Hey.
-Is that funny?

728
00:52:11,503 --> 00:52:13,171
-Hey, don't.
-Let go of me.

729
00:52:13,255 --> 00:52:16,216
-Do you find this funny, you jerk?
-Hey, come here.

730
00:52:16,299 --> 00:52:20,011
I have some good news for you.

731
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:22,848
It's finally time for

732
00:52:23,348 --> 00:52:25,976
the school trip
that we've all been waiting for!

733
00:52:32,440 --> 00:52:33,441
Aren't you guys happy?

734
00:52:33,525 --> 00:52:35,235
-I hate school.
-It's not just school.

735
00:52:35,318 --> 00:52:36,611
It's a school "trip."

736
00:52:36,695 --> 00:52:38,530
You'll be spending
two nights away from home.

737
00:52:38,613 --> 00:52:39,656
I love it!

738
00:52:39,739 --> 00:52:41,116
This is so annoying.

739
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:43,827
-Can we not go?
-You have to go.

740
00:52:44,369 --> 00:52:46,496
This is an extension of classes.

741
00:52:46,580 --> 00:52:48,665
Then why don't Hwi-yeong and Jun-u

742
00:52:48,748 --> 00:52:51,626
arrange the schedule
for the school trip? Okay?

743
00:52:51,793 --> 00:52:52,794
Yes, sir.

744
00:52:55,338 --> 00:52:57,340
You all remember the school trip
last year, right?

745
00:52:57,424 --> 00:52:59,384
There's no need for us to waste time.

746
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:03,471
People who like dancing can prepare
for the talent show.

747
00:53:03,555 --> 00:53:04,723
Pil-sang, put your hand down.

748
00:53:04,806 --> 00:53:05,849
And...

749
00:53:05,932 --> 00:53:08,059
We go on a school trip just once a year.

750
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:11,396
Why don't we throw
some memorable event together?

751
00:53:14,774 --> 00:53:17,944
Jun-u. The finals and performance
assessments are coming up soon.

752
00:53:18,028 --> 00:53:19,112
And there's the mock exam too.

753
00:53:19,195 --> 00:53:20,864
Let's not waste time
on unnecessary things.

754
00:53:24,743 --> 00:53:25,785
Then...

755
00:53:26,244 --> 00:53:28,914
Why don't those of us who want
to enjoy our school trip

756
00:53:28,997 --> 00:53:30,665
prepare something fun?

757
00:53:31,416 --> 00:53:34,336
Not those who think it's a waste of time.

758
00:53:35,170 --> 00:53:36,296
That sounds good.

759
00:53:37,005 --> 00:53:38,131
I agree.

760
00:53:38,340 --> 00:53:39,382
Me too.

761
00:53:43,303 --> 00:53:44,471
That sounds okay.

762
00:53:44,930 --> 00:53:47,265
Then those who agree to
Jun-u's opinion can stay.

763
00:53:47,349 --> 00:53:48,558
The others can go.

764
00:53:49,351 --> 00:53:50,352
What do you think?

765
00:54:01,196 --> 00:54:02,364
Soo-bin, thank you.

766
00:54:03,365 --> 00:54:04,449
For staying.

767
00:54:10,997 --> 00:54:12,791
Ro-mi, aren't you going
to the group study?

768
00:54:12,874 --> 00:54:14,292
No. I'm staying.

769
00:54:15,001 --> 00:54:16,169
Me too.

770
00:54:17,837 --> 00:54:19,881
Guys, this is the only school trip
this year.

771
00:54:19,965 --> 00:54:22,175
Why don't we all participate?

772
00:54:24,469 --> 00:54:25,595
Don't go?

773
00:54:25,804 --> 00:54:27,430
It's time for our study group.

774
00:54:36,856 --> 00:54:37,899
Lee Gi-tae.

775
00:54:40,568 --> 00:54:41,611
Don't go.

776
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:48,994
She's right. Don't go.

777
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:51,287
Gi-tae, you should join us.

778
00:54:51,371 --> 00:54:52,747
You're the student life leader.

779
00:55:02,590 --> 00:55:03,591
I'm sorry.

780
00:55:07,095 --> 00:55:08,638
My god, this is unbelievable.

781
00:55:08,722 --> 00:55:09,764
He left.

782
00:55:29,492 --> 00:55:30,535
Shall we gather around?

783
00:55:32,370 --> 00:55:36,082
Why don't we try something unique
and all wear hanboks?

784
00:55:36,416 --> 00:55:37,834
To promote Korean traditions.

785
00:55:38,001 --> 00:55:39,961
Don't you think the vice-principal
will love that?

786
00:55:40,045 --> 00:55:44,132
Hey. Are we throwing a party
for your grandma or what?

787
00:55:45,633 --> 00:55:48,595
Wearing the same outfit
sounds like a good idea.

788
00:55:48,678 --> 00:55:50,472
Yes, it sounds good.

789
00:55:51,473 --> 00:55:52,891
It doesn't sound bad.

790
00:55:59,689 --> 00:56:00,774
How about this?

791
00:56:02,650 --> 00:56:05,445
We can all wear old clothes
from each of our homes.

792
00:56:05,528 --> 00:56:08,698
This is what I wore on my first date
when I was 18.

793
00:56:08,907 --> 00:56:10,408
Our parents' clothes

794
00:56:11,201 --> 00:56:12,702
that are filled with fond memories.

795
00:56:14,204 --> 00:56:15,497
That sounds good.

796
00:56:15,580 --> 00:56:17,665
But what should I wear?

797
00:56:17,791 --> 00:56:19,334
Retro cosplay?

798
00:56:24,672 --> 00:56:26,091
O-je, wear something cool.

799
00:56:26,925 --> 00:56:27,967
Okay.

800
00:56:28,218 --> 00:56:29,469
What is "retro"?

801
00:56:30,428 --> 00:56:31,471
English.

802
00:56:31,805 --> 00:56:32,639
Prepare something.

803
00:56:32,722 --> 00:56:35,058
Our class vice president's idea is great.

804
00:56:35,391 --> 00:56:36,392
I like it.

805
00:56:38,603 --> 00:56:40,271
It will look really great

806
00:56:41,439 --> 00:56:42,565
if we all wear them.

807
00:56:42,732 --> 00:56:44,567
-Right.
-It will look really cool.

808
00:56:44,651 --> 00:56:46,402
-Yes.
-It will look so pretty, right?

809
00:56:46,486 --> 00:56:48,696
-Yes, it will.
-Hey, thanks.

810
00:56:55,620 --> 00:56:58,540
She got off work around this time,
so she's probably still here.

811
00:57:15,181 --> 00:57:16,224
Hello.

812
00:57:23,523 --> 00:57:24,566
Mr. Oh.

813
00:57:25,233 --> 00:57:27,485
Jun-u, why did you come to work so early?

814
00:57:27,569 --> 00:57:30,864
Oh, the girl who works before me
said she had to leave early.

815
00:57:32,740 --> 00:57:34,659
Oh, really?

816
00:57:35,743 --> 00:57:36,786
Yes.

817
00:57:38,455 --> 00:57:41,166
Is there something you wanted
to say to me?

818
00:57:42,750 --> 00:57:43,751
Yes.

819
00:57:45,253 --> 00:57:47,505
I heard your meeting
with the kids went very well.

820
00:57:47,589 --> 00:57:50,925
You know...
That retro cosplay or something.

821
00:57:54,220 --> 00:57:56,764
You didn't have to come
all the way here to tell me that.

822
00:57:57,223 --> 00:58:01,728
I just felt so proud of you
and wanted to give you a hug.

823
00:58:01,811 --> 00:58:02,812
Good job.

824
00:58:04,439 --> 00:58:05,857
All right, then.

825
00:58:17,702 --> 00:58:19,621
Hwi-yeong, how did your study group go?

826
00:58:19,996 --> 00:58:21,539
I had some more work to do after.

827
00:58:21,623 --> 00:58:22,749
What are you doing here?

828
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:26,878
Nothing much.
I'm just enjoying the breeze.

829
00:58:30,381 --> 00:58:32,217
You know, our school trip event...

830
00:58:33,259 --> 00:58:34,385
Can't you join us?

831
00:58:34,928 --> 00:58:36,429
Everybody talks about it now.

832
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:39,724
It's a competition among all the classes.
If we win,

833
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:42,101
we'll get an extra air purifier
in our classroom,

834
00:58:42,185 --> 00:58:44,729
and we each get two gift certificates too.

835
00:58:45,021 --> 00:58:46,689
We came up with an idea today.

836
00:58:46,773 --> 00:58:50,026
It'd be great if everyone
in the class participates.

837
00:58:50,693 --> 00:58:53,071
You're our class president after all?

838
00:58:57,992 --> 00:58:59,744
Fine, then. Whatever.

839
00:59:01,496 --> 00:59:02,914
Suit yourself.

840
00:59:05,833 --> 00:59:07,210
If you grant me my wish.

841
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:12,382
We came here often
when we were in elementary school.

842
00:59:12,465 --> 00:59:13,591
After our private lessons.

843
00:59:14,425 --> 00:59:15,510
Behind our moms' backs.

844
00:59:16,302 --> 00:59:17,303
We did.

845
00:59:17,387 --> 00:59:20,348
And whenever my mom caught me,
she practically killed me.

846
00:59:21,057 --> 00:59:24,143
But I didn't know
these game machines were still here.

847
00:59:24,352 --> 00:59:25,311
I know.

848
00:59:25,395 --> 00:59:27,313
Shall we begin, then?

849
00:59:27,522 --> 00:59:28,648
-Okay.
-Let's begin.

850
00:59:28,731 --> 00:59:29,732
Okay.

851
00:59:31,025 --> 00:59:32,360
The game began.

852
00:59:47,417 --> 00:59:48,835
Hwi-yeong, what are you doing?

853
00:59:48,918 --> 00:59:50,712
What if your mom catches you
playing games?

854
00:59:50,795 --> 00:59:51,921
Just go.

855
00:59:59,596 --> 01:00:01,055
What do you want now?

856
01:00:01,556 --> 01:00:02,724
I told you to go.

857
01:00:02,807 --> 01:00:03,975
I don't want to.

858
01:00:05,101 --> 01:00:06,853
My dad told me

859
01:00:06,936 --> 01:00:10,607
that if I saw a sad friend,
then just sit next to him.

860
01:00:11,065 --> 01:00:12,525
Without saying anything.

861
01:00:12,609 --> 01:00:15,153
That's how we share each other's troubles.

862
01:00:19,157 --> 01:00:19,991
Soo-bin.

863
01:00:22,619 --> 01:00:23,620
I feel happy.

864
01:00:30,335 --> 01:00:31,336
I just...

865
01:00:32,587 --> 01:00:35,590
suddenly felt uncomfortable
going out with someone.

866
01:00:37,383 --> 01:00:38,509
Suddenly

867
01:00:39,385 --> 01:00:40,470
during a movie.

868
01:00:57,278 --> 01:00:59,489
This thought came to my mind.

869
01:01:00,740 --> 01:01:05,203
That you must have liked me a lot.

870
01:01:08,039 --> 01:01:09,040
You liked me so much

871
01:01:10,041 --> 01:01:12,377
that you wanted to show me

872
01:01:13,086 --> 01:01:14,962
that text from Jun-u.

873
01:01:19,425 --> 01:01:21,511
Even though you knew it would hurt me.

874
01:01:27,433 --> 01:01:29,560
Was that a moment's jealousy?

875
01:01:36,109 --> 01:01:37,110
I'm sorry.

876
01:01:37,777 --> 01:01:41,030
I was just a bit worried about you.

877
01:01:41,114 --> 01:01:44,367
I'm sorry too
for making you feel that way.

878
01:01:45,493 --> 01:01:48,413
We're old friends.
We're closest friends, right?

879
01:01:58,673 --> 01:02:02,385
Oh, my. This playground
looks completely different now.

880
01:02:02,468 --> 01:02:05,221
There was only sand
when we were little, right?

881
01:02:06,139 --> 01:02:07,890
It's so much better, right?

882
01:02:13,855 --> 01:02:14,856
See you.

883
01:02:14,981 --> 01:02:18,860
I've granted you your wish, so you'll
prepare for the school trip with us, okay?

884
01:02:20,194 --> 01:02:21,946
Bye. Good night.

885
01:02:38,838 --> 01:02:40,173
I can't believe this.

886
01:02:41,507 --> 01:02:44,302
What is this?
What did I walk you home for?

887
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:48,014
I'll give you another chance
some other time.

888
01:02:48,473 --> 01:02:51,392
Forget it. No more chances left.

889
01:02:52,018 --> 01:02:53,019
Go now.

890
01:02:55,772 --> 01:02:56,773
Soo-bin.

891
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:00,443
Well...

892
01:03:04,155 --> 01:03:05,823
-That day...
-What?

893
01:03:10,870 --> 01:03:11,829
Actually,

894
01:03:12,789 --> 01:03:14,832
the text...

895
01:03:15,666 --> 01:03:16,709
Soo-bin.

896
01:03:23,549 --> 01:03:25,593
I thought about it,
but it just can't be true.

897
01:03:27,094 --> 01:03:29,222
That you suddenly felt uncomfortable
during the movie.

898
01:03:33,059 --> 01:03:35,061
What are you doing at this hour?

899
01:03:35,645 --> 01:03:37,897
I have a feeling that
there's been a misunderstanding.

900
01:03:39,565 --> 01:03:40,608
Because

901
01:03:41,526 --> 01:03:43,319
your eyes said something else.

902
01:03:47,740 --> 01:03:48,783
What is it?

903
01:03:54,956 --> 01:03:56,082
Later.

904
01:04:03,214 --> 01:04:04,215
Soo-bin.

905
01:04:04,382 --> 01:04:06,717
She says she doesn't want to talk.

906
01:04:06,801 --> 01:04:07,802
Hwi-yeong.

907
01:04:09,095 --> 01:04:10,263
Stay out of it.

908
01:04:12,723 --> 01:04:13,724
Soo-bin.

909
01:04:19,146 --> 01:04:21,357
Go home, Soo-bin. I'll send him back.

910
01:04:38,499 --> 01:04:40,001
Did you believe this?

911
01:04:42,962 --> 01:04:44,130
More than you believe me?

912
01:04:51,929 --> 01:04:53,014
I see.

913
01:05:03,441 --> 01:05:05,109
I did it for you.

914
01:05:05,568 --> 01:05:06,944
I can explain everything.

915
01:05:59,246 --> 01:06:02,375
O-je, do you know where Jun-u lives?

916
01:06:02,541 --> 01:06:04,835
Don't you feel sorry for Soo-bin?

917
01:06:05,419 --> 01:06:06,837
You hurt her.

918
01:06:07,088 --> 01:06:08,714
I think I'll need some time.

919
01:06:08,923 --> 01:06:11,467
Please don't take too long. I'm sorry.

920
01:06:11,968 --> 01:06:15,012
Hwi-yeong, I want you to give some thought

921
01:06:15,096 --> 01:06:16,931
to how you feel about me.

922
01:06:17,014 --> 01:06:19,600
Thank you for coming here yourself
when you're busy.

923
01:06:20,309 --> 01:06:21,560
Wait, Ji-min.

924
01:06:22,478 --> 01:06:24,855
While we're at it, let's win!

925
01:06:24,939 --> 01:06:26,315
Two!

926
01:06:27,149 --> 01:06:29,652
Next up is Go Dong. He's coming--

927
01:06:29,735 --> 01:06:31,112
Is that you, Jun-u?

928
01:06:48,045 --> 01:06:50,256
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

